==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heliographic
<hw>He`li*o*graph"ic</hw>
<pr>(h⟦emac⟧`l⟦icr⟧*⟦osl⟧*gr⟦acr⟧f"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a description
of the sun.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Heliographic</xex> longitudes and latitudes of
spots on the sun's surface are analogous to geographic longitudes and
latitudes of places on the earth.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to heliography or a heliograph;
made by heliography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Heliographic chart</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Chart</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heliography</ent>⟦br⟧
